Course Enrollment System
Overview

The Course Enrollment system is the central access-control system of the platform.

Instead of checking:

Did the student purchase the course?
Did the student redeem an access code?

The platform checks only:

Does the student have an active enrollment for this course?

This creates a clean and scalable architecture.

Enrollment Philosophy

All access methods eventually lead to:

CourseEnrollment

This means:

Access Code
→ CourseEnrollment

Online Purchase
→ CourseEnrollment

Future Admin Grant
→ CourseEnrollment

Future Free Courses
→ CourseEnrollment

The system separates:

How access was obtained

from:

Whether the student currently has access

This improves:

Scalability
Maintainability
Security
Access control consistency
