Access Codes System
Overview

The Access Codes system allows students to unlock courses using unique activation codes.

The system is designed to support:

Offline sales
Physical store distribution
Promotional codes
Scholarship access
Future partnerships
Access Code Structure

Each code:

8 characters
Uppercase letters + numbers
Globally unique
Linked to one course
Single-use only
Can be disabled
Supports expiration dates

Example:

A7K9P2QX
M3Z8TR1B
Database
Main Access Code Table
access_codes_accesscode

Fields:

id
code
course_id
is_used
is_active
used_by_id
created_by_id
used_at
expires_at
created_at
Code Generation System

Codes are generated automatically by the backend.

The system guarantees uniqueness by:

Checking the database before saving

Generated characters use:

A-Z
0-9
Why Codes Are NOT Generated Automatically With Courses

The platform intentionally separates:

Course Creation

from:

Access Code Generation

Reason:

Courses may:

Still be incomplete
Remain unpublished
Not require access codes
Need different quantities later

This gives Admin users full control.

Access Code Generation API
Admin Only

Endpoint:

POST /api/access-codes/generate/

Request Example:

{
  "course_id": 1,
  "count": 50,
  "expires_at": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

The backend generates multiple unique codes for the selected course.

Access Code Redemption
Student Flow

Student enters:

Activation code

Backend validates:

Code exists
Code is active
Code is unused
Code is not expired
Student does not already own the course

If valid:

Create CourseEnrollment
Mark code as used
Store used_by
Store used_at
Transaction Safety

The redemption process uses:

transaction.atomic()

Purpose:

Prevent partial database updates.

Without this protection:

Possible issue:

Enrollment created
BUT code not marked as used

This could create inconsistent data.

Atomic transactions ensure:

Everything succeeds
OR everything rolls back
Access Code APIs
Generate Codes
POST /api/access-codes/generate/

Admin only.

Redeem Code
POST /api/access-codes/redeem/

Authenticated students only.

Purchase System
Overview

The platform includes an internal purchase system designed to simulate real online payments.

The architecture is already prepared for future integration with:

Stripe
PayPal
HyperPay
PayTabs
Purchase Philosophy

The system separates:

Payment processing

from:

Course access

Meaning:

Purchase completed
→ Create CourseEnrollment

The payment provider NEVER directly controls access.

This creates a provider-independent architecture.

Purchase Database
Main Purchase Table
purchases_purchase

Fields:

id
student_id
course_id
amount
status
provider
provider_reference
completed_at
created_at
updated_at
Purchase Status System

Available statuses:

pending
completed
failed
cancelled
refunded

Purpose:

Track the entire payment lifecycle.

Internal Purchase Flow
Step 1

Student clicks:

Buy Course

Backend creates:

Purchase(status="pending")
Step 2

Temporary internal endpoint completes purchase:

pending → completed
Step 3

Backend automatically creates:

CourseEnrollment
Duplicate Purchase Protection

The system prevents duplicate pending purchases.

If the student clicks the Buy button multiple times:

The backend reuses the existing pending purchase

instead of creating multiple payment records.

This protects against:

Double-clicks
Slow internet
UI lag
Duplicate transactions
Enrollment Duplication Protection

The system also prevents:

Duplicate course ownership

using:

unique(student, course)

This ensures:

A student can never own the same course twice.

Future Real Payment Integration

The architecture is already prepared for real payment gateways.

Future flow:

Student clicks Buy
→ Redirect to payment gateway
→ Gateway webhook verifies payment
→ Purchase becomes completed
→ Enrollment is created

Important:

The existing business logic will NOT need to be rewritten later.

Only the payment provider integration layer will be added.

Frontend Purchase Experience
Course Cards

Each course card now includes:

Course details button
Purchase button
Purchase Modal Behavior

When clicking:

Buy Course

The student sees two options:

Option 1 — Redeem Access Code

Student enters:

Activation code

Frontend calls:

POST /api/access-codes/redeem/
Option 2 — Online Purchase

Frontend calls:

POST /api/purchases/create/

Then temporarily:

POST /api/purchases/{id}/complete/

This simulates successful payment until a real gateway is integrated later.

Dynamic Course Ownership

The frontend receives:

has_access

inside the Course API response.

Example:

{
  "has_access": true
}

This allows the frontend to:

Hide Buy button
Show "You Own This Course"

without additional requests.

